      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 58 of a 12-week money program. The script targets the fear-of-depletion pattern that sits beneath held-back generosity: the sense that money given away is money gone, that the return is uncertain, that giving from a small pile is risky. The reframe moves toward giving as part of the same circulation that brings money in.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to tapping? Read ",
